The paper deals with properties of planar graphs and their generalizations, which are typically studied in computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves analyzing the edge density of these graph families, which is a topic of interest in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
